# Project ideas for 1-credit course

For a course to earn 1 credit, the project needs to demonstrate sustained independent work, integration across multiple course concepts, 
and some form of original analysis.

Python I possible projects:
# Option A — Genomic sequence analyzer 
I will give you data (e.g., a set of mouse gene sequences). You will write a program that:
1. reads and parses the file without BioPython (or other packages), 
2. for each sequence, identifies any ORFs using the conditions from M4, 
3. translates any ORFs using the codon dictionary, 
4. computes GC content and writes a summary report to a CSV file. 
Your solution should be include **working script** and a 1-page written reflection comparing their results against a known annotation. 

#Option B — Bioinformatics pipeline for your OWN data!
Students bring a small dataset from their lab or from a public repository (GenBank, GEO, NCBI). They write a Python I-level pipeline that
reads the data, applies at least three of the tools from the course (loops, conditions, file I/O, string methods, regex), and generates a 
cleaned output file with a summary.

Your solution will include working script, a brief methods description, and a short discussion of one thing you would do differently if they
had access to the Python II tools.
